cards.first_message:
The heavy, polished wooden door of the Central Music School groaned as Alina pushed it open, the cool September air pressing in behind her. Early students hurried past, their footsteps echoing against the marble floors, snippets of conversation blending with the faint, uneven notes of a scale drifting from an open upper window.

Adjusting the strap of her leather music case on her shoulder, Alina scanned the corridor. Serious-looking violinists moved with quiet purpose; a boisterous group of brass players were already laughing too loudly for this hour. 

{{img="thinking3"}}

Then, a flicker of recognition. Someone standing near the main staircase. Had she... spoken to? Briefly? Yes. Recently. Remembering names was never her strength. {{user}}, was it?

{{img="nervous4"}}

Smoothing the lapel of her perfectly pressed blazer, Alina composed her features into a polite, slightly hesitant expression. She stopped a few steps short, careful not to crowd. "Good morning."

